{"article_id":"JqRmGPf459IjNRx0","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Trump administration on Monday moved to end asylum protections for most Central American migrants in a major escalation of the president 's battle","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to tamp down the number of people","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"crossing the U.S.-Mexico border .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"According to a new rule","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"published in the Federal Register ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"asylum seekers","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"who pass through another country first","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"will be ineligible for asylum at the U.S. southern border .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The rule ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"expected to go into effect on Tuesday ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"also applies to children","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"who have crossed the border alone .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"There are some exceptions :","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"If someone has been trafficked ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"if the country","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"the migrant passed through","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"did not sign one of the major international treaties","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"that govern how refugees are managed","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"( though most Western countries have signed them )","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"or if an asylum-seeker sought protection in a country","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"but was denied ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"then a migrant could still apply for U.S. asylum .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"But the move by President Donald Trump 's administration was meant to essentially end asylum protections","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"as they now are on the southern border .","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"The policy is almost certain to face a legal challenge .","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"U.S. law allows refugees to request asylum","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"when they arrive at the U.S.","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"regardless of how they did so ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"but there is an exception for those","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"who have come through a country","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"considered to be `` safe . ''","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"But the Immigration and Nationality Act ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"which governs asylum law ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"is vague on how a country is determined `` safe '' ;","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"it says","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"`` pursuant to a bilateral or multilateral agreement . ''","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Right now , the U.S. has such an agreement ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"known as a `` safe third country , ''","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"only with Canada .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Under a recent agreement with Mexico , Central American countries were considering a regional compact on the issue ,","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"but nothing has been decided .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Guatemalan officials were expected in Washington on Monday ,","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"but apparently a meeting between Trump and Guatemalan President Jimmy Morales was canceled amid a court challenge in Guatemala","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"over whether the country could agree to a safe third with the U.S .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"The new rule also will apply to the initial asylum screening ,","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"known as a `` credible fear '' interview ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"at which migrants must prove","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"they have credible fears","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"of returning to their home country .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"It applies to migrants","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"who are arriving to the U.S. ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"not those","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"who are already in the country .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Trump administration officials say","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"the changes are meant to close the gap between the initial asylum screening","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"that most people pass","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"and the final decision on asylum","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"that most people do not win .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"But immigrant rights groups , religious leaders and humanitarian groups have said","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"the Republican administration 's policies amount to a cruel and calloused effort","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"to keep immigrants out of the country .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"Guatemala , Honduras and El Salvador are poor countries","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"suffering from violence .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"Along with the administration 's recent effort","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to send asylum seekers back over the border ,","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Trump has tried to deny asylum to anyone","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"crossing the border illegally","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and restrict who can claim asylum ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and Attorney General William Barr recently tried to keep thousands of asylum seekers detained","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"while their cases play out .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Nearly all of those efforts have been blocked by courts .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"Meanwhile , conditions have worsened for migrants","depth":3},{"id":72,"text":"who make it over the border","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"seeking better lives .","depth":4},{"id":74,"text":"Tens of thousands of Central American migrant families cross the border each month ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"many claiming asylum .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"The numbers have increased","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"despite Trump 's derisive rhetoric and hard-line immigration policies .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Border facilities have been dangerously cramped and crowded well beyond capacity .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"The Department of Homeland Security 's watchdog found fetid , filthy conditions for many children .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"And lawmakers","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"who traveled there","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"recently decried conditions .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Immigration courts are backlogged by more than 800,000 cases ,","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"meaning many people wo n't have their asylum claims heard for years","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"despite move judges being hired .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"People are generally eligible for asylum in the U.S.","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"if they feared return to their home country","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"because they would be persecuted","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"based on race , religion , nationality or membership in a particular social group .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"During the budget year for 2009 , there were 35,811 asylum claims ,","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"and 8,384 were granted .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"During 2018 budget year , there were 162,060 claims filed ,","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"and 13,168 were granted .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":187,"left":164,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":134,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":115,"right":133,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":105,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":96,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":0,"right":95,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":100,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":97,"right":99,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":97,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":98,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":98,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":101,"right"